cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper deals with protecting the confidentiality of machine learning models, which is a security concern, making cs.CR the most likely sub-category. The paper specifically focuses on deep neural networks (DNNs), which are commonly used in machine learning, making cs.LG and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the use of DNNs in image classification, which falls under cs.CV. Finally, the proposed approach for detecting model extraction attacks involves analyzing the distribution of queries over time, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
